# AI Operations Assistant Environment

## Production-Grade OpenEnv-Compliant Environment for Enterprise AI Workflows

![Status](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-production-brightgreen)
![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.10%2B-blue)
![OpenEnv](https://img.shields.io/badge/openenv-compliant-blue)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-green)

---

## üéØ Overview

This is a **production-quality, OpenEnv-compliant environment** designed for training and evaluating AI agents on realistic enterprise business workflows. It simulates real-world complexity in:

- **Email Management** ‚Äî Classification, prioritization, and response handling
- **Support Ticket Management** ‚Äî Issue triage, escalation, and resolution
- **Meeting Scheduling** ‚Äî Coordinating calendars with urgency awareness

The environment implements **dense reward signals**, **task dependencies**, and **realistic constraints** to train agents that work like actual operations teams.

---

## üöÄ Key Features

### ‚úÖ OpenEnv Compliance

- Strict adherence to OpenEnv specification
- `reset()` ‚Üí `Observation`
- `step(Action)` ‚Üí `(Observation, Reward, done, info)`
- `state()` ‚Üí complete environment state
- Full type safety with Pydantic models

### ‚úÖ Rich Entity System

- **Emails**: Subject, body, priority, category, handle status
- **Support Tickets**: Issue, severity, status, resolution tracking
- **Meeting Requests**: Time, participants, urgency, scheduling status

### ‚úÖ Dense Reward Function

```text
+0.3  ‚Üí Correct email classification
+0.4  ‚Üí Appropriate support reply
+0.5  ‚Üí Correct ticket resolution
+0.3  ‚Üí Timely meeting scheduling
+0.2  ‚Üí Correct spam detection
-0.5  ‚Üí Incorrect critical escalation
-0.3  ‚Üí Wrong action taken
-0.05 ‚Üí Per-step efficiency penalty
```

### ‚úÖ Three Progressive Tasks

1. **üü¢ Easy** ‚Äî Email classification only (50 steps)
2. **üü° Medium** ‚Äî Email + ticket handling (75 steps)
3. **üî¥ Hard** ‚Äî Full operations with prioritization (120 steps)

### ‚úÖ Deterministic Grading System

- Score 0.0 ‚Üí 1.0 for each task
- No randomness in evaluation
- Clear, auditable metrics

### ‚úÖ Baseline Agent

- Rule-based keyword matching
- Reproducible performance
- Benchmark for comparison

